OL,3,CThe light bulb moment that led one
OL,4,Cwoman to give a helping hand
OL,6,FFast forward three years, the group
OL,7,Fhas moved premises and the need for
OL,8,Ftheir services has grown beyond their
OL,9,Fexpectations.
OL,11,FSitting down to take part in UTV's
OL,12,FGoing the Extra Mile podcast, Louise
OL,13,Ftells me that people come looking not
OL,14,Fjust for financial and practical help
OL,15,Fbut even to stay warm in their hub, to
OL,16,Ffind company and chat.
OL,18,F"When people are down, they're really
OL,19,Fdown," Louise says.JLouise points to
OL,20,Fthe rising cost of living as a key
OL,21,Fdriver for poverty.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/11
