OL,3,CThe light bulb moment that led one
OL,4,Cwoman to give a helping hand
OL,6,F"Just go into the supermarket. Look at
OL,7,Fthe cost of food. How can people be
OL,8,Fexpected to survive?" she said.
OL,10,FShe recounts the story of a young
OL,11,Fwoman who came to the hub early one
OL,12,Fmorning, crying because she had no
OL,13,Ffood for her children and had had no
OL,14,Felectricity for three days.
OL,16,FAfter supplying her with food for
OL,17,Fbreakfasts and lunch, Louise describes
OL,18,Fthe satisfaction of being able to help
OL,19,Fsomeone like that.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
